<p class="">There are precedents. The last one which is directly in point, which concerned the qualifications of an hon. Member of this House, occurred in 1913, and related to Sir Stuart Samuel. That matter was referred to the Judicial Committee, which gave advice to the House upon it.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
